s all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":89,"region":89,"country":125,"address":126,"geo":127},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":128,"lon":129},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":131,"mainLang":132,"languages":133},"Ancient Greek","grc",[131],{"type":135,"bibl":136},"edition",[137,149],{"type":138,"n":139,"citedRange":140,"ptr":141,"ref":143,"title":145,"author":33,"date":146,"citation":147,"uri":148},"bulletin","SEG","43.0634",{"target":142},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ",{"_":144,"target":144},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum","1923-","\u003Cspan>‘Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum’, \u003Ci>Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum\u003C/i>, 1923, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/F2GG87EQ",{"author":150,"date":151,"citedRange":152,"ptr":153,"ref":155,"inscriptionDate":151,"title":157,"citation":158,"uri":159},"Manganaro","1993","583 n.102 fig.20",{"target":154},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JBI7CI5R",{"_":156,"target":156},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001827","Greco nei pagi e latino nelle città della Sicilia romana tra I e VI sec. d.C.","\u003Cspan>Giacomo Manganaro, «Greco nei pagi e latino nelle città della Sicilia romana tra I e VI sec. d.C.», in \u003Ci>l’epigrafia del villaggio\u003C/i>, a c. di A. Calbi, A. Donati, e G. Poma (Faenza, 1993), 543–94\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/JBI7CI5R",{"type":161,"bibl":162},"discussion",[19],{"editor":164,"principal":167,"contributors":168,"change":184},{"_":165,"ref":166},"Jonathan Prag"