 class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: Γ; the vertical is compatible with Γ, Ι, Τ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: [μ]ητ[ροπόλεως]; part of the Mu is clearly visible on the stone.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":229,"html":230},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":232,"html":233},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The restoration proposed by Manganaro for line 2 is clearly plausible and aligns with the width suggested by the proposed restoration of line 3. The production of a public text of this sort in Greek in the later imperial period is notable, even if the text cannot be closely dated.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":235,"html":236},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 43.0634 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1993 583 n.102 fig.20 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001827\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001827\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":238,"html":239},"handnote","\u003Cp>Tall, fairly narrow letters, but well spaced, simply cut with minimal serifs. Beta and Rho have very small eyes (closed). Alpha with straight bar.\u003C/p> Line 1-4  55-60  Interlineation line 1 to 2  7  Interlineation line 2 to 3  8-12  Interlineation line 3 to 4  7-8  ",{"id":241,"html":242},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence ",[244,246,249,250],{"html":245},"Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2015-03-25, magazzino B, cassa 19 (inventory number not identified)",{"id":247,"lang":132,"html":248},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-